  "texts": [
    "Mathematically, it is represented as: Let, 𝑆 = {𝑠 1, 𝑠 2, 𝑠 3, ------𝑠 𝑛 } be the set of n-states representing different entity label and, 𝑂 = {𝑜 1, 𝑜 2, 𝑠 3, ------𝑜 𝑚 } be the set of m-observations, representing words in the text.",
    "Each feature 𝑓 𝑘 ( 𝑠 𝑡-1, 𝑠 𝑡, 𝑜 𝑡) captures a specific aspect of the data relevant to labeling.",
    "Each feature function 𝑓 𝑘 has an associated weight say λ 𝑘 that determines its contribution to the overall labeling probability.",
    "The probability of sequence of labels given a sequence of observations is given by equation (4).𝑃(𝑦|𝑥) = 1 𝑧(𝑥) exp ( ∑ ∑ λ 𝑘 𝑓 𝑘 ( 𝑘 𝑚 𝑡=1 𝑦 𝑡-1, 𝑦 𝑡, 𝑥 𝑡))(4) (c) Decision TreeIt is a technique that makes decisions by recursively splitting the dataset into subsets based on the values of input features.",
    "It creates a tree like structure where each internal node represents decision based on a feature, and each leaf node represents an outcome."
